-- Advanced Computer Program for controlling the Mining Turtle with Remote Console Control and ID Prompt
local computerID
local modem = peripheral.wrap("top")  -- Replace "top" with the side where the modem is attached

-- Function to send commands to the turtle
local function sendCommand(command)
    modem.transmit(computerID, computerID, command)  -- Send command to turtle using its ID
end

-- Function to execute a console command on the turtle
local function executeConsoleCommand(command)
    modem.transmit(computerID, computerID, command)  -- Send command to turtle using its ID
    local _, _, senderID, message = os.pullEvent("modem_message")
    if senderID == computerID then
        print("Turtle console output:")
        print(message)
    else
        print("Unexpected response received")
    end
end

-- Function to prompt user for turtle ID
local function promptForTurtleID()
    term.clear()
    term.setCursorPos(1, 1)
    print("Enter Turtle ID:")
    return tonumber(read())  -- Read user input and convert to number (assuming turtle ID is numeric)
end

-- Main function to run the program
local function main()
    computerID = promptForTurtleID()

    if not computerID then
        print("Invalid Turtle ID entered. Exiting program.")
        return
    end

    while true do
        term.clear()
        term.setCursorPos(1, 1)
        print("=== Mining Turtle Remote Control Panel ===")
        print("[1] Mine Chunk")
        print("[2] Return")
        print("[3] Inventory")
        print("[4] Refuel All")
        print("[5] Shutdown Turtle")
        print("[Q] Quit")

        local _, key = os.pullEvent("key")
        if key == keys.one then
            sendCommand("mine_chunk")
        elseif key == keys.two then
            sendCommand("return")
        elseif key == keys.three then
            sendCommand("inventory")
        elseif key == keys.four then
            executeConsoleCommand("refuel all")
        elseif key == keys.five then
            sendCommand("shutdown")
            break
        elseif key == keys.q or key == keys.Q then
            break  -- Quit the program
        end
    end
end

-- Run the main function
main()

title: Python bubblesort perftest - 12x5
content:
import random
import time
import sys

def bubble_sort(arr):
    n = len(arr)
    for i in range(n-1):
        for j in range(0, n-i-1):
            if arr[j] > arr[j+1]:
                temp = arr[j]
                arr[j] = arr[j+1]
                arr[j+1] = temp
    return arr

MINF = 0
MAXF = 16777216

TESTS = 12
SECS = 5

TIME = SECS * 1000000000

def test() -> int:
  c = 0
  done = time.time_ns() + TIME
  while time.time_ns() < done:
    arr = []
    for i in range(200):
      arr.append(float(random.randint(MINF, MAXF)))

    bubble_sort(arr)
    c += 1

  return c

sumOps = 0

for i in range(TESTS):
  ops = test()
  sumOps += ops
  print(f'{SECS} seconds - {ops} arrays')

print(f'Average: {int(sumOps/TESTS)} arrays for {SECS} seconds')
print(f'         {int(sumOps/TESTS/SECS)} arrays per second')

import chess
import time
from itertools import permutations, combinations
from functools import lru_cache

@lru_cache(maxsize=None)
def simplify_fen_string(fen):
    parts = fen.split(' ')
    simplified_fen = ' '.join(parts[:4])  # Zachov√°v√°me pouze informace o pozici
    return simplified_fen

# Startovn√≠ pozice
start_fen = "6k1/8/5Q2/6K1/8/8/8/8 w - - 0 1"
simplified_POZ2 = simplify_fen_string(start_fen)
POZ = {1: simplified_POZ2}

AR = {simplify_fen_string(start_fen): {'used': 0, 'to_end': None}}
N = 1
M = 0

start_time = time.time()

def format_elapsed_time(elapsed_time):
    hours, remainder = divmod(elapsed_time, 3600)
    minutes, seconds = divmod(remainder, 60)
    return f"{int(hours)}h {int(minutes)}m {int(seconds)}s"

def print_elapsed_time(total_time, level_time):
    print(f"{format_elapsed_time(total_time)} / {format_elapsed_time(level_time)}")

while M < N:
    M += 1
    current_fen = POZ[M]
    board = chess.Board(current_fen)
    simplified_current_fen = current_fen

    if AR[simplified_current_fen]['used'] == 0:
        AR[simplified_current_fen]['used'] = 1
        for move in board.legal_moves:
            board.push(move)
            POZ2 = board.fen()
            simplified_POZ2 = simplify_fen_string(POZ2)

            if simplified_POZ2 not in AR:
                AR[simplified_POZ2] = {'used': None, 'to_end': None}

            if AR[simplified_POZ2]['used'] is None:
                N += 1
                POZ[N] = simplified_POZ2
                AR[simplified_POZ2] = {'used': 0, 'to_end': None}

            board.pop()  # Vr√°t√≠me tah zpƒõt

print(f"Poƒçet pozic je {N}")

# P≈ôid√°n√≠ kontroly pro mat, rem√≠zu a v√Ωchoz√≠ hodnotu
F = 0
for i in range(1, N + 1):
    current_fen = POZ[i]
    board = chess.Board(current_fen)
    simplified_current_fen = simplify_fen_string(current_fen)

    if board.is_checkmate():
        AR[simplified_current_fen]['to_end'] = -1000
        F += 1
    elif board.is_stalemate() or board.is_insufficient_material() or board.is_seventyfive_moves() or board.is_fivefold_repetition():
        AR[simplified_current_fen]['to_end'] = 0
    else:
        AR[simplified_current_fen]['to_end'] = 0

print(f"Poƒçet pozic v matu je {F}")

uroven = 0
while F > 0:
    uroven += 1
    level_start_time = time.time()
    print(f"V√Ωpoƒçet v √∫rovni {uroven}")
    
    F = 0
    current_level_positions = 0
    for i in range(1, N + 1):
        current_fen = POZ[i]
        board = chess.Board(current_fen)
        simplified_current_fen = simplify_fen_string(current_fen)
        if AR[simplified_current_fen]['to_end'] == 0:
            hod = -2000
            for move in board.legal_moves:
                board.push(move)
                POZ2 = board.fen()
                simplified_POZ2 = simplify_fen_string(POZ2)
                hod2 = -AR[simplified_POZ2]['to_end']
                if hod2 > hod:
                    hod = hod2
                board.pop()  # Vr√°t√≠me tah zpƒõt
            if hod == 1001 - uroven:
                AR[simplified_current_fen]['to_end'] = 1000 - uroven
                F += 1
                current_level_positions += 1
            if hod == -1001 + uroven:
                AR[simplified_current_fen]['to_end'] = -1000 + uroven
                F += 1
                current_level_positions += 1
    level_end_time = time.time()
    total_elapsed_time = level_end_time - start_time
    level_elapsed_time = level_end_time - level_start_time
    print(f"Nalezeno {current_level_positions} pozic v √∫rovni {uroven}")
    print_elapsed_time(total_elapsed_time, level_elapsed_time)

print(f"Nalezeno {F} pozic celkem")

# V√Ωpis v≈°ech pozic s to_end == 21
print("Pozice s to_end == 17:")
for fen, data in AR.items():
    if data['to_end'] < 983 and data['to_end'] != 0:
        print(f"{fen} -> to_end: {data['to_end']}")

current_fen = POZ[1]
board = chess.Board(current_fen)
simplified_current_fen = simplify_fen_string(current_fen)
hod = AR[simplified_current_fen]['to_end']
print(f"Hodnocen√≠ poƒç√°teƒçn√≠ pozice je {hod}")

local computerConfig = computerConfigTemplate
local elevatorConfig = {}

local main = basalt.createFrame()
local mainThread = main:addThread()
local secondThread = main:addThread()

local function StartCheckHost()
    
    main:removeChildren()

    headerCheckHost:setPosition(1,1)
    headerCheckHost:setSize("parent.w", 5)
    headerCheckHost:setTextAlign("center")

    local progressBarCheckHost = main:addProgressbar()
    progressBarCheckHost:setProgress(0)
    progressBarCheckHost:setSize("parent.w / - 10", 3)
    progressBarCheckHost:setPosition(5, "parent.h / 2")
    
    local function CheckHost()
        rednet.broadcast({"Iam Host?", computerConfig.computerID, computerConfig.computerPosition}, hostCheckProtocol)
        local id, message = rednet.receive(hostCheckProtocol, 10)
        if not id then
            computerConfig.isComputerHost = true
            table.insert(elevatorConfig, computerConfig)
        else
            computerConfig.isComputerHost = false
        end
        startProgram()
    end
    local function animateProgrssBar()
        local progressValue = 0
        while true do
            if progressValue == 100 then break end
            os.sleep(1)
            progressValue = progressValue + 10
            progressBarCheckHost:setProgress(progressValue)
        end
    end
    mainThread:start(CheckHost)
    secondThread:start(animateProgrssBar)
end

local function eleInit()
    if fs.exists("eleConfig.txt") == false then 
        local headerLabel = main:addLabel()
        headerLabel:setPosition("parent.w /2 - 32",3)
        headerLabel:setText("Elevator Initialization")
        headerLabel:setFontSize(2)
        headerLabel:setTextAlign("center")

        local eleNumberLabel = main:addLabel()

                computerConfig.elevatorID = eleNumberInput:getValue()
            end
        end
        eleNumberInput:onChange(inputOnChange)

        local eleRsInputLabel = main:addLabel()

        local eleRsInputDropDown = main:addList()

        eleRsInputDropDown:addItem("Front")

            computerConfig.rsBcInputSide = item.text
        end)

        local eleRsOutputLabel = main:addLabel()
        eleRsOutputLabel:setPosition(2,19)
        eleRsOutputLabel:setText("Redstone Bundled Cable Output Side ")

        local eleRsOutputDropDown = main:addList()
        eleRsOutputDropDown:setPosition(2,20)
        eleRsOutputDropDown:addItem("Top")
        eleRsOutputDropDown:addItem("Bottom")
        eleRsOutputDropDown:addItem("Left")
        eleRsOutputDropDown:addItem("Right")
        eleRsOutputDropDown:addItem("Front")
        eleRsOutputDropDown:addItem("Back")
        eleRsOutputDropDown:onChange(function(self, item)
            computerConfig.rsBcOutputSide = item.text
        end)

        local saveButton = main:addButton()
        saveButton:setSize(10,3)
        saveButton:setPosition("parent.w - 11", "parent.h - 4")
        saveButton:setText("Save")

            if(event=="mouse_click")and(button==1)then
                if eleNumberInput:getValue() ~= "" then
                    computerConfig.elevatorID = eleNumberInput:getValue()
                else
                    basalt.debug("Error: You need to enter a Elevator ID")
                    return
                end
                computerConfig.computerPosition.x, computerConfig.computerPosition.y, computerConfig.computerPosition.z =  gps.locate(2, false)
                protocol = ("Elevator %d"):format(computerConfig.elevatorID)
                hostCheckProtocol = protocol .. " HostCheck"
                StartCheckHost()
            end
        end)
    else
        --read config file and load into elevatorFloorConfig
    end
end





local function listenRednetForMember()
    while true do
        local id, message = rednet.receive(hostCheckProtocol, 10)
        if computerConfig.isComputerHost  == true then
            if message[1] == "Iam Host?" then
                local floorFound = false
                for floor in ipairs(eleFloorConfig) do
                    if floor.compID == message[2] then
                        rednet.send(compID, floor, hostCheckProtocol)
                        floorFound = true
                        break
                    end
                end
                if floorFound == false then
                    local floorConfig = computerConfigTemplate

                    floorConfig.compID = message[2]
                    floorConfig.compWorldPosition.x = message[3][1]
                    floorConfig.compWorldPosition.x = message[3][2]
                    floorConfig.compWorldPosition.x = message[3][3]

                    table.insert(elevatorConfig, floorConfig)
                end
            end
        else
            if message[1] == "Iam Host?" then
                rednet.send(compID, "NO!", hostCheckProtocol)
            end
        end
    end
end


local function startProgram()
    mainThread:stop()
    secondThread:stop()
    main:removeChildren()
    if isComputerHost == true then
        local headerHostMain = main:addLabel()
        headerHostMain:setPosition(1,1)
        headerHostMain:setSize("parent.w", 5)
        headerHostMain:setTextAlign("center")
        headerHostMain:setFontSize(2)
        headerHostMain:setText(("Elevator %d Controlboard"):format())
        --HostMonitorGUI elevatorConfig[1] 
    else 
        --FloorMonitorGUI elevatorConfig[>1]
    end
    mainThread:start(listenRednetForMember)
end

-- First Config Screen



eleInit()
basalt.autoUpdate()

"""
Created on Mon Jun  3 14:20:25 2019
"""

import boto3
from boto3.dynamodb.conditions import Key
import pandas as pd

dynamodb = boto3.resource("dynamodb")

def query_all(table, **kwargs):
    """Performs a query operation on the specified Amazon DynamoDB table and returns all items.

    Arguments:
    table -- str, the name of the table to perform the query operation on
    **kwargs -- additional keyword arguments to be passed to the `query` method of Amazon DynamoDB

    Returns:
    list, a list of items obtained from the query operation, with any Decimal objects
        converted to floats
    """
    fres = []

    tres = dynamodb.Table(table).query(**kwargs)
    fres += tres["Items"]

    while "LastEvaluatedKey" in tres:
        tres = dynamodb.Table(table).query(
            ExclusiveStartKey=tres["LastEvaluatedKey"], **kwargs
        )
        fres += tres["Items"]

    return decimal_to_float(fres)


res = query_all(
    "email_events_data",
    KeyConditionExpression=Key("campaign_name").eq("SOFTWAREENGINEERAIT"),
)

df = pd.json_normalize(res)
df.to_csv("SOFTWAREENGINEERAIT.csv", index=False)

content:
#!/home/ec2-user/miniconda3/bin/python
"""
This module sends email notifications to recipients whose
email addresses are stored in a CSV file. The message body of
the email is defined in a separate module named "variables".
This module utilizes the AWS SES service to send the emails.
"""
import csv
import time
from datetime import datetime, timedelta
from email.mime.multipart import MIMEMultipart
from email.mime.text import MIMEText

import boto3
from botocore.exceptions import ClientError

from variables import (
    AWS_ACCESS_KEY,
    AWS_SECRET_KEY,
    BODY,
    CAMPAIGN_NAME,
    RECIPIENT_CSV_PATH,
    SENDER_,
    SUBJECT,
)

utc_time = datetime.utcnow()
ist_offset = timedelta(hours=5, minutes=30)
ist_time = utc_time + ist_offset
formatted_ist_time = ist_time.strftime("%Y-%m-%d %H:%M:%S")

SENDER = SENDER_
AWS_REGION = "ap-south-1"
CHARSET = "utf-8"

# Create a new SES resource
client = boto3.client(
    "sesv2",
    region_name=AWS_REGION,
    aws_access_key_id=AWS_ACCESS_KEY,
    aws_secret_access_key=AWS_SECRET_KEY,
)

email_list = []


# Read the recipient email addresses from the CSV file
recipient_list = []
mapping = {}
with open(RECIPIENT_CSV_PATH, newline="") as csvfile:
    reader = csv.DictReader(csvfile)
    for row in reader:
        recipient_list.append(row["Emails"].strip())

print("Total number of recipients: ", len(recipient_list))


rate_limit = 100  # Maximum number of emails per second

total_time_ = time.time()
for i, recipient_email in enumerate(recipient_list):
    # Try to send the email
    try:
        message = MIMEMultipart("alternative")
        message["Subject"] = SUBJECT
        message_body_part = MIMEText(BODY, "html")
        message.attach(message_body_part)
        response = client.send_email(
            FromEmailAddress=SENDER,
            Destination={
                "ToAddresses": [
                    recipient_email,
                ],
            },
            ReplyToAddresses=[SENDER],
            Content={"Raw": {"Data": message.as_string()}},
            EmailTags=[
                {"Name": "anchor-campaign", "Value": CAMPAIGN_NAME},
            ],
            ConfigurationSetName="track-creator-mail",
            # ListManagementOptions={
            #     'ContactListName': 'MyWasyEmailContactList',
            #     'TopicName': 'LocalTestGuys'
            # }
        )
        print(f"{formatted_ist_time} - Email {i+1} sent successfully.")
    except ClientError as err:
        print(err.response["Error"]["Message"])

    # Delay to stay within the rate limit
    if (i + 1) % rate_limit == 0 and (i + 1) != len(recipient_list):
        time.sleep(1)

print("Total time taken: ", time.time() - total_time_)
print("Total number of emails sent: ", len(recipient_list))

class Solution:
    def surfaceArea(self, grid: List[List[int]]) -> int:
        n = len(grid)
        res = 0
        for i in range(n):
            rh = 0
            ch = 0
            for j in range(n):
                t = grid[i][j]
                res += 2 if t else 0
                res += abs(t - rh)
                rh = t
                t = grid[j][i]
                res += abs(t - ch)
                ch = t
            res += rh + ch
        return res

local function checkFile(path)
    local file = io.open(path, "r")

        return true

    end

-- –§—É–Ω–∫—Ü–∏—è –¥–ª—è —Å–∫–∞—á–∏–≤–∞–Ω–∏—è —Ñ–∞–π–ª–∞ —Å Pastebin

local function displayProgress(progress, total)
    local width = 62  -- –®–∏—Ä–∏–Ω–∞ –ø—Ä–æ–≥—Ä–µ—Å—Å-–±–∞—Ä–∞
    local filled = math.floor((progress / total) * width)

end

-- –§—É–Ω–∫—Ü–∏—è –¥–ª—è –æ—Ç–æ–±—Ä–∞–∂–µ–Ω–∏—è —Å—Ç–∞—Ç—É—Å–∞ —Ñ–∞–π–ª–æ–≤
local function displayFiles(files, currentDir, currentFile)
    local folderWidth = math.floor(screenWidth / 3)
    local positions = {
        ["/home/"] = {x = folderWidth / 2 - 7, y = 12},
        ["/.lib/"] = {x = folderWidth * 3 / 2 - 7, y = 12},
        ["/etc/"] = {x = folderWidth * 5 / 2 - 7, y = 12}
    }

    for dir, fileList in pairs(files) do
        local pos = positions[dir]
        local x, y = pos.x, pos.y
        local allFilesInstalled = true
        for _, file in ipairs(fileList) do
            if not checkFile(dir .. file.name) then
                allFilesInstalled = false
                break
            end
        end
        local dirColor = allFilesInstalled and color_folder_installed or color_folder_pending
        if dir == currentDir then
            dirColor = color_folder_installing
        end
        gpu.setForeground(dirColor)
        gpu.set(x, y, "‚îå‚îÄ" .. dir)
        gpu.set(x, y + 1, "‚îÇ")
        for i, file in ipairs(fileList) do
            local fullPath = dir .. file.name
            local color = (dir == currentDir and file.name == currentFile) and color_file_installing or
                    (checkFile(fullPath) and color_file_installed or color_file_pending)
            gpu.setForeground(color)
            gpu.set(x, y + 1 + i, "‚óâ " .. file.name)
        end
        gpu.setForeground(dirColor)
        gpu.set(x, y + 1 + #fileList + 1, "‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îÄ‚îò")
    end

end

-- –§—É–Ω–∫—Ü–∏—è –¥–ª—è —Ü–µ–Ω—Ç—Ä–∏—Ä–æ–≤–∞–Ω–∏—è —Ç–µ–∫—Å—Ç–∞

gpu.set(logo_x, logo_y + 2, "|_____  |    \\_    |    ______|    |    |     | |_____      |_____| ______|")

-- –û—Ç–æ–±—Ä–∞–∂–µ–Ω–∏–µ –ø–æ–¥–∑–∞–≥–æ–ª–æ–≤–∫–∞
gpu.set(header_x, header_y, "–í–æ—Å—Å—Ç–∞–Ω–æ–≤–ª–µ–Ω–∏–µ —Å–∏—Å—Ç–µ–º—ã. –ü—Ä–æ–≤–µ—Ä–∫–∞ –Ω–∞—á–∞–ª—å–Ω—ã—Ö —Ñ–∞–π–ª–æ–≤:")

-- –ê–Ω–∏–º–∞—Ü–∏—è —É—Å—Ç–∞–Ω–æ–≤–∫–∏ —Ñ–∞–π–ª–æ–≤
local function installFiles()
    for dir, fileList in pairs(files) do
        for _, file in ipairs(fileList) do
            term.clear()
            -- –û—Ç–æ–±—Ä–∞–∂–µ–Ω–∏–µ –ª–æ–≥–æ—Ç–∏–ø–∞
            gpu.set(logo_x, logo_y, "_______  ______ __   __ _______ _______ _______              _____  _______")
            gpu.set(logo_x, logo_y + 1, "|       |_____/   \\_/   |______    |    |_____| |           |     | |______")
            gpu.set(logo_x, logo_y + 2, "|_____  |    \\_    |    ______|    |    |     | |_____      |_____| ______|")
            -- –û—Ç–æ–±—Ä–∞–∂–µ–Ω–∏–µ –ø–æ–¥–∑–∞–≥–æ–ª–æ–≤–∫–∞
            gpu.set(header_x, header_y, "–í–æ—Å—Å—Ç–∞–Ω–æ–≤–ª–µ–Ω–∏–µ —Å–∏—Å—Ç–µ–º—ã. –ü—Ä–æ–≤–µ—Ä–∫–∞ –Ω–∞—á–∞–ª—å–Ω—ã—Ö —Ñ–∞–π–ª–æ–≤:")
            -- –û—Ç–æ–±—Ä–∞–∂–µ–Ω–∏–µ —Ñ–∞–π–ª–æ–≤
            displayFiles(files, dir, file.name)
            -- –°–∫–∞—á–∏–≤–∞–Ω–∏–µ —Ñ–∞–π–ª–∞
            if file.address then
                downloadFile(file.address, dir .. file.name)
            end
            -- –û—Ç–æ–±—Ä–∞–∂–µ–Ω–∏–µ –ø—Ä–æ–≥—Ä–µ—Å—Å-–±–∞—Ä–∞
            local startTime = computer.uptime()
            while (computer.uptime() - startTime) <= 2 do -- –ó–∞–≥—Ä—É–∑–∫–∞ –≤ —Ç–µ—á–µ–Ω–∏–µ 2 —Å–µ–∫—É–Ω–¥
                displayProgress(computer.uptime() - startTime, 2)
                os.sleep(0.05) -- –û–±–Ω–æ–≤–ª–µ–Ω–∏–µ –∫–∞–∂–¥—ã–µ 50 –º–∏–ª–ª–∏—Å–µ–∫—É–Ω–¥
            end
            displayProgress(2, 2) -- –ó–∞–≤–µ—Ä—à–µ–Ω–∏–µ –ø—Ä–æ–≥—Ä–µ—Å—Å–∞
        end
    end
end

installFiles()
